    <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;" >
        8.4 You may also make an early repayment of a portion of the credit at any time
        (without penalty or premium). Any such early repayment will be applied to the amount
        due on the next rescheduled payment date (and any excess to the amounts due on the
        following repayment date(s)). Upon any such partial early repayment the amounts
        payable on the remaining repayment dates shall be recalculated by applying the applicable
        interest rate applied to the outstanding balance of the credit. Any such changes
        will be reflected on the dashboard and in the statement of account which you can
        also access via the dashboard.</p></dd>
</dl>
<dl>
    <dt style="margin-left: 30px;"><b>9. Undertakings</b></dt>
    <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;" >
        9.1 The Customer shall immediately notify the Creditor of an Event of Default occurring.</p></dd>
    <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;" >
        9.2 The Customer shall not, nor shall it permit any Subsidiary (defined below),
        to:-
        <dl>
            <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 90px;" >
