            </p></dd>
            <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 90px;" >
                (d) make any change in the nature of business conducted; and/or</p></dd>
            <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 90px;" >
                (e) assignment its rights or obligations under this Agreement to a third party;
                without the prior written consent of the Creditor.</p></dd>
        </dl>
    </p></dd>
    <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;" >
        9.3 The Customer shall, and shall procure that any Subsidiary, shall as necessary:-
        <dl>
            <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 90px;" >
                (a) obtain, renew and comply with all necessary certificates, licences, permits,
                consents or other authorisations required for the purposes of its business; and</p></dd>
            <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 90px;" >
                (b) comply with all applicable laws, regulations or other legal requirements.</p></dd>
        </dl>
    </p></dd>
    <dd><p  style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;" >
        9.4 The Customer shall promptly supply the Creditor with such information regarding
        the financial affairs of the Customer and any company which is or becomes a subsidiary
        of the Customer within the meaning of Section 736 of the Companies Act 1985 ("Subsidiary"),
